About Us
Our Story
On March 15th, 1986 Gerry McHugh moved from a small farming village in County Galway in the west of Ireland to Boston, Massachusetts. At the time he was a 20-year-old immigrant but he came to this country full of ambition and with a willingness to work in order to make his American dream come true. Gerry worked ...

McHugh's was my first bar experience when I moved to Lakeland several months ago. It is a great Irish Pub and I could even say it is better than one I frequented in Winter Garden. They have great pricing compared to other Pubs; however, one thing I miss from my original Pub is the options on Food.
